## Introduction

Hello everyone,
My name is Dhanvi Bhat, and I am a Computer Science student at Dayananda Sagar University in Bangalore. I have a CGPA of 8.5 in my B.Tech studies and scored 91.5% in my 12th grade at Alvas Pre-University College.
I am deeply passionate about technology and have worked on several interesting projects. One of the project is the Signature Classification using Deep Learning, where I developed an advanced predictive model to categorize signatures into their respective human classes.
Another significant project I worked on is the Integrated IoT Water Quality Kit. In this project, I designed a comprehensive water quality analysis system utilizing IoT technology. I integrated various sensors like DS18B20, DHT11, Turbidity, and TDS with an ESP32 microcontroller for real-time monitoring. The data is transmitted to the Thingspeak cloud server via Wi-Fi, enabling remote water quality assessment and analysis through a scalable web interface.
In addition to my technical projects, I have received couple of achievements. I was awarded a Letter of Appreciation for my exceptional contribution in demonstrating IoT projects at the 'From Concepts to Reality: Connecting the Dots' workshop organized by Malnad College of Engineering, Hassan. I was also selected at the college level to participate in the Smart India Hackathon (SIH).
My technical skills include programming in Python and C, working with frameworks like TensorFlow, Keras, and Scikit-Learn, and using SQL for database management. I am also familiar with tools like ThingSpeak and MySQL WorkBench.In addition, I have experience with front-end languages such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
In addition to my technical abilities, I have good organizational and time-management skills, effective communication, and the ability to work both independently and as part of a team
I have also volunteered as an intern at the Under 25 Summit 2023, where I was involved in various activities, including sales, design, team management, and communication.
I am fluent in several languages, including English, Hindi, Kannada, Marathi, Tulu, and have a basic understanding of Japanese.
I am excited to connect with you all!
Thank you for your time.
